    "headerDoc": "STEP 892 — Sierpinski, Riesel, Brier Numbers (Tier S #5-6)\n  ============================================================\n\n  Sierpinski number: odd k such that k·2^n + 1 is composite for ALL n ≥ 1.\n  Smallest conjectured: k = 78,557.\n  Open: is 78557 the smallest Sierpinski number?\n  Currently the remaining 5 candidates < 78557 are:\n    21181, 22699, 24737, 55459, 67607\n\n  Riesel number: odd k such that k·2^n − 1 is composite for ALL n ≥ 1.\n  Smallest conjectured: k = 509,203.\n\n  Brier number: k that is BOTH Sierpinski and Riesel.\n  Smallest known < 10^28.\n\n  Status: all OPEN for smallest.\n\n  "
